 Justification:
 FY 2027 funding required to procure FALCO components. APKWS with FALCO software is an effective, low-cost munition against adversary UASs. This munition is a preferred alternative to using costly/
 exquisite weapons for the air-to-air C-UAS mission. APKWS is critical to combat adversary drone and UAS attacks against US and partner forces.

 FY 2027 funds will procure 1,793 Single Variant Block Upgrade guidance sections, 6,293 proximity fuses, and 254 rocket pod launchers. Components and rocket pods are necessary to build and launch the
 AURs.

 Note: Procurement quantities can change based on negotiated options/pricing bands and available funding, in accordance with Title 10, U.S Code Section 2308 BUY-TO-BUDGET ACQUISITION.

 Funds increased from FY 2026 to FY 2027 to address increase in FALCO procurements.




