 Justification:
 FY2027 funding will be used to address Diminished Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS).

 FY2025 - Received $123 million in Tranche funding to replenish inventory that was expended during Operations.

 FY2025 and FY2026 Funding will be used for Un-definitized Contract Action (UCA) Effort, warhead purchase, non-recurring engineering, analysis and studies, integration, test, qualification, production readiness
 and operational readiness of engineering change proposals to resolve safety, reliability or other operational deficiencies, decrease weapon system cost, preserve future production capabilities and capacities, and
 meet Congressional, National Agency and Department of War mandates.

 Funding includes any Diminishing Manufacturing Source and Material Shortages (DMSMS) to include MOP's Actuator Controller Electronic Control Unit (ECU), joint mission computer, SABR-Y (GPS
 receiver), Inertial Measurement Unit (IMU) power supply card, Fuze Interface Electronics (FIE) Box Assembly, Electromagnetic Interface (EMI) Filer Box Assembly, and procurement of MOP assets for warheads,
 guidance kits, fuzes, and associated support equipment.




