 Description:
 The B-52H is a long-range strategic bomber capable of delivering the widest variety of nuclear and conventional standoff and direct attack munitions in the Air Force. The Air Force maintains 76 B-52Hs in its
 inventory. The Air Force plans to fly the B-52H to 2050 or beyond. The B-52H is averaging 12,128 flight hours for the entire fleet as of December 2025. This is an average from January - December of 2025.

 This line item funds modifications to the B-52H aircraft.

 The FY 2027 request for B-52 includes $422,399 thousand of discretionary and $23,600 thousand of mandatory for a total of $455,999 thousands. The mandatory funds B-52 is for the ROCS program to
 purchase 55 TACKits to complete the temporary modification bringing capability to the warfighter ahead of the germinate MOD solution.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
 defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.

 Funding for the exhibit contained in PE 0101113F. Funding under this PE may be used to alleviate Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS) issues, including Life of Type Buys.
