 Description:
 Program Description: MISSILE REPLENISHMENT SPARES. The Missile Replenishment Spares program funds all ballistic and non-ballistic missile replenishment spares. The replenishment and repair
 spare parts are needed to support and maintain ballistic and non-ballistic missile systems. Replenishment spares include such items as rocket motors, cables, telemetry packages, and electronic components.
 Procurements will include spares with long production lead items.

 The following Major Defense Acquisition Programs (MDAP) have funding in this line:
 AMRAAM, 185
 SDB II, 439
 AIM-9X Blk II, 442
 MM III, 401

 This program has associated Research Development Test and Evaluation funding in PEs 11120F, 11213F, 27161F, 11122F, and 27163F.

 The MM III FY25 rescission of $13.643M is not reflected in this budget documentation.




