 Description:
 The Advanced Pilot Training (APT)/ T-7A Red Hawk program will replace the Air Education Training Commands (AETC) aging T-38C fleet with new aircraft, Ground Based Training Systems (simulators, training
 devices, computer based training systems, academics, etc.), Maintenance Training Systems (which will be procured via a separate contracting action), and support infrastructure currently used in the Advanced
 Fighter/Bomber Fundamentals Course.

 FY 2027 Advanced Pilot Training T-7A Advanced Procurement funding will support T-7A air vehicle long lead parts and materials necessary to protect delivery schedule. Advanced procurement funding will be
 used towards the air vehicle suppliers/systems based on the long lead time associated with material.

 This program, Advanced Pilot Training T-7A Advanced Procurement, is a new start.




