 Description:
 The C-37C aircraft will recapitalize the C-37A/B fleet with a common mission design series (MDS) in support of the Executive Airlift small aircraft mission. The recapitalization will consist of a minimum of 17
 aircraft. Sixteen aircraft to recapitalize the existing C-37A/B fleet and one additional aircraft will address training deficiencies. The Common Small EA Replacement Aircraft program is based on modifying a
 commercial derivative aircraft with very important person (VIP) interiors, a distinguished visitor (DV) compartment, integrated mission communication, and self-defense systems. To meet emerging national
 security threats and address capacity challenges, AMC requires a fleet of aircraft capable of carrying up to five crew and twenty personnel on non-stop trips up to 7,500 miles anywhere in the world.

 C-37 funding will also support Program Support Costs (PSC) activities, Advisory & Assistance Services (A&AS), Other Government Costs (OGC). Future years will include interim supply support for additional
 aircraft and support equipment.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0401314F.




