Justification:
FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $48.885 million funds the Trojan NexGEN and Tactical Communication and Video-Teleconferencing Capability (TCVC) system requirements in support of
Southern Borders and INDOPACOM AORs:

(BA0331) -
FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $11.477 million will support Trojan NexGen Family of Systems (FoS). Funding is used for the procurement of material (hardware/software) in support of
planned Trojan NexGEN upgrades and issuing activities to include fixed and mobile collection (BA0331). NexGEN funds will be used to procure the following:

Two (2) Trojan Analytical Node (TAN) - $546K
Three (3) Remote Operations Facility (ROF) - $1,005K
One (1) Remote Collections Facility (RCF) - $3,090K

Funds in the amount of $6,836K will be used to modernize and field NexGEN FoS.

(BA0333) -
FY 2027 Base procurement dollars in the amount of $37.408 million will fund TCVC systems. This is based on a shift in program requirements from SPIRIT Phase IV to a TCVC system. Funding will support
the engineering, integration, fielding, and training of the TCVC systems. Funding will also support the TROJAN Network Control Center (TNCC)/TROJAN Network Operations Center (TNOC) interface upgrades
(BA0333). Base funds will be used to procure the following:

64 TCVC Systems - $26,368K
12 TCVC Spares - $4,332K

Funds in the amount of $6,708K will be used to modernize the TNCC and issuing activities.




