 Justification:
 This program, OTHACF Automated Test Systems, is a new start.
 This program, B01B00 B-1B Squadrons, is a new start.
 This program, H060WM HH60W Modifications, is a new start.
 This program, OSAEA0 VC-25B, is a new start.

 Aerial Targets: FY 2027 funding request is to procure spare parts for the Air Force Subscale Aerial Target (BQM-167A) to include initial replacement components, equipment and parts.

 Precision Attack Systems Procurement: FY 2027 funding request for procurement of initial spares to support and maintain Advanced Targeting Pods modified with enhanced combat identification, longer range
 target location, improved imagery processing and target identification. Efforts will reduce collateral damage, and increase fratricide prevention for F-15E, F-16, A-10, B-1B, and B-52. Spares will include major
 sub-components such as mid-wave and long wave infrared cameras, mission processors and controllers, and redesigned data links for encryption, as well as eye-safe lasers for use in urban environments.

 B-1B Squadrons - This is an FY27 New Start - initial readiness spares are required to support the fielding multiple new B-1 capabilities in the FYDP. FY 2027 funding request will buy initial spares for B-1 Hybrid
 Satellite Communications (SATCOM).

 B-2 Squadrons: FY 2027 funding will buy initial spares for B-2 communication programs, including Advanced Communications System (ACS) 4.0, B-2 Battlespace Collaborative Combat Communications, Digital
 High Frequency, and Hybrid Satellite Communications; plus Radar Modernization Program (RMP), B-2 displays, Military GPS User Equipment and Modular Rotary Launcher Assembly.

 B-52: FY 2027 funding request procures the last year of initial spares to support operations for the B-52 Radar Modernization Program (RMP) which supports nuclear and conventional operations by replacing
 the current APQ-166 radar on the B-52H aircraft with the AN/APQ-188 radar. The use of new technology will increase both the overall reliability of the radar system and the capabilities for new missions. RMP will
 allow the operational command (AF Global Strike Command) to fully utilize the capabilities of the B-52H aircraft to employ an array of weapons and perform mission-essential navigation and weather avoidance
 functions.

 C-130 Airlift Squadrons: No FY 2027 funding requested.

 C-17: FY 2027 funding request addresses deficiencies in C-17 Readiness Spares Package (RSP) inventory to enable new Agile Combat Employment (ACE) mission requirements. Provides deployable spares
 to support C-17 maintenance and repair during initial combat or contingency operations without resupply for 30 days. Additionally, this request procures initial spares for on-going modification programs to include
 but not limited to Beyond Line of Sight (BLOS), Replacement Heads-Up Display (RHUD), Filter Fire Mitigation (FFM), Aircraft Connectivity, training systems, and other production efforts.


