Appropriation / Budget Activity / Budget Sub Activity:                                                      P-1 Line Item Number / Title:
3010F: Aircraft Procurement, Air Force / BA 06: Aircraft Spares and Repair Parts /                          000999 / Initial Spares/Repair Parts
BSA 10: Aircraft Spares and Repair Parts
ID Code (A=Service Ready, B=Not Service Ready):                         Program Elements for Code B Items: N/A                                   Other Related Program Elements: N/A
Line Item MDAP/MAIS Code: N/A
 F-35 Squadrons: FY 2027 funding request supports the necessary production lead time for procurement of initial spares for Air Vehicle, Propulsion and Site Activation and Hardware for new production aircraft
 in Lot 20 and Depot Lay in spares required for F135 engine overhaul maintenance. Funding supports the Air Force's (AF) unique Deployed Spares Packages (DSP) to ensure AF requirements align with
 Operational Plans for Combatant Commanders. The AF share of the JSF Global Spares Pool (GSP) costs ensure proper inventory levels to support daily training and operational USAF Fleet sustainment
 activities. The GSP is a foundational tenet of the F-35 joint program, whereby the USAF, Navy, Marine Corps, seven international partners and twelve Foreign Military Sales (FMS) customers share the cost
 of spares, eliminating the need for each individual Participant to procure their own full depth and range of spares. Funding supports readiness initiatives to increase Mission Capable (MC) rates across the
 Enterprise and ensures procurement of spares at required levels to meet sustainment milestones for all participants.

 HH60W MODS: Due to an inadvertent database error, $7.0M of FY 2027 funding in P-1 Line #61, was intended for this line (P-1 Line P-68). This funding is intended to start AFDW Operational Flight Trainer
 spares procurement in FY 2027. FY 2027 funding request is to procure HH-60W initial spares and initial repair parts for including, but not limited to, components impacted by Diminishing Manufacturing Sources,
 spare parts for simulators and training devices, and spare components for modification efforts to support the HH-60W fleet and the Air Force District of Washington transfer and modification.

 KC-135S: FY 2027 funding request procures initial spares required to support Real Time Information in the Cockpit (RTIC) and Mobility Air Forces (MAF) Connectivity Programs for critical communications and
 situational awareness capabilities.

 KC-46: FY 2027 funding request is for initial spares parts pipeline and repair spare parts to include but not limited to spare engines to support newly fielded KC-46A aircraft and Air Mobility Command's bed-down
 plan, as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D. FY 2027 funds will be used to competitively procure initial spares using multiple-award IDIQ contracts.

 MQ-9 UAV: FY 2027 funding request to procure minimal level of spares for Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO) and MQ-9 Multi-Domain Operations (M2DO) kits as part of the modification schedule for the fleet.

 RC-135 (Manned Reconnaissance Systems): FY 2027 funding request to procure initial spares in support of modifications of three different RC-135 aircraft mission design series utilizing seven separate
 engineering baselines. The initial spares consist of numerous non-stock listed, commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) LRU's, SRU's and piece part electronic components necessary for initial fielding and operations at
 seven world-wide operating locations.

 Advanced Pilot Training (APT)/T-7A: FY 2027 funding request for initial spares to include but not limited to airframe, engine, readiness, and training systems to support the T-7A aircraft and devices.

 MH-139A: FY 2027 funding request for initial spares to include but not limited to airframe, engine, readiness, and training systems to support the MH-139A aircraft.

 VC-25B: FY 2027 funding request for fully mission capable spares to include but not limited to airframe, engine, readiness, and training systems to support the VC-25B aircraft and devices.

 Automated Test Systems: FY2027 funding will be used to replenish Electronic Warfare spares kit package inventories to meet Combatant Command Requirements.




