 Description:
 Theater SIGINT System (B99755): TSIGS provides Army commanders with a forward deployable, remote or locally controlled, signals intelligence (SIGINT) system for contingency operations. TSIGS, made up of
 the Trojan Soldier Portable Remote Intelligence Group (TSPRING) and Picketline, are currently fielded. This program funds CLS for HW/SW support, HW sustainment including depot repairs, spares, technology
 refresh, maintenance and operational readiness. Enables integration with sustained capabilities in support of theater aligned Military Intelligence units and Intelligence Community (IC) collection priorities, as well
 as Transformation in Contact (TiC) initiatives, Presidential Directives and Operational Needs Statements.

 Special Purpose Systems (BZ9751): Program funds Technical Insertions (TIs) for the ground-based Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) system with additional capabilities required by fielded units to effectively engage
 enemy forces and provide Force Protection information to friendly forces. This program funds procurement of Government and Commercial Off-the-Shelf (GOTS/COTS) Next Generation Signals Intelligence
 (SIGINT) capabilities for the Prophet system to pace near peer, emerging threats, and other Signals of Interest (SOIs) to support the National Defense Strategy. Prophet enables integration, interoperability, and
 force modernization with emerging capabilities in support of Multi-Domain Operations.

 FY 2026 BZ9751 Special Purpose Systems funding was transferred from Budget Activity (BA) 2, BZ9750 MOD OF IN-SVC EQUIP (INTEL SPT) to BA 2, B97600 Terrestrial layer Systems (TLS)/ B97612 -
 SPECIAL PURPOSE SYSTEM INTEL SPT.

