 Justification:
 FY 2025: $22.078 million - Supported planned hardware/software upgrades and technical refreshes for Cyber Analytics, Enterprise Perimeter Defense, Endpoint Security, and Thunderdome capabilities. This
 evolution and expansion of cyber capabilities was critical to meeting mission requirements, including FY 2024 National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA) directives. These efforts enabled DISA to facilitate
 Defense Agencies and Field Activities (DAFAs) adoption of Zero Trust capabilities, increase full packet capture and performance monitoring, and expand data compliance across DISA and the DoW.

 In FY 2025, DISA acquired the following capabilities:

 • Cyber Analytics: $2.319 million - FY 2025 funding supported the deployment of 15 EndaceProbes at Internet Access Points (IAPs), increasing their capacity by 20 GBps. These efforts increased the
 EndaceProbe population to 76. The EndaceProbe appliance provides accurate, full packet capture and simultaneously hosts and integrates with network and application performance monitoring tools. This
 capability also provides a critical network recording history to solve cybersecurity, network, and application issues.

 • Perimeter Defense – Secret Internet Protocol Router Releasable (SIPR REL): $2.310 million - Supported critical tech refresh for the SIPR REL function within the Perimeter Defense capability with procurement
 of network switches at four sites and a lab (five total). This effort supported sharing of classified and intelligence information with Five Eye mission partners.

 •Thunderdome: $17.449 million - Procured an additional 414 Software-Defined Wide Area Network (SD-WAN) units to expand capabilities to DAFAs, such as Defense Threat Reduction Agency (DTRA) and
 Defense Logistics Agency (DLA). SD-WAN units enabled routing traffic to/from remote locations securely and efficiently.

 FY 2026: $6.254 million - Funding completes work on SIPR REL and initiates Enterprise Perimeter – Enterprise Break & Inspect (EBI) tech refresh to comply with FY 2024 NDAA.

 • Perimeter Defense – SIPR REL: $2.133 million - Funding supports obtaining F5 Hardware and software/licensing to continue supporting sustainment of enhanced authentication to SIPR via SIPR REL. The
 same four sites and lab (five total) receiving FY 2025 tech refresh require Hardware/Software to be fully operational in FY 2026.

 • Enterprise Perimeter Defense: $4.121 million - Funding supports critical tech refresh for the EBI Function within the Enterprise Perimeter Defense Capability with planned procurement of F5 hardware and
 software licenses at two of ten DISA IAP locations. This effort increases decryption throughput of outbound traffic at two of the ten DISA IAP locations. The EBI Capability also provides critical analysis of
 incoming and outbound data to detect cyber security threats. These tech refresh efforts enable critical updates of crucial F5 System Level Components.

 Explanation of Change from FY 2025 to FY 2026: -$15.824 million - Decrease due to completion of EndaceProbe requirement and the conclusion of Thunderdome SD-WAN rollout.




