 Description:
 The F-15EX is a new multirole-capable fighter jet based on the 2-seat F-15QA (Qatar) configuration, upgraded with advanced capabilities, including the Eagle Passive Active Warning Survivability System
 (EPAWSS) and USAF F-15 Continuous Delivery & Integration (CD&I) Operational Flight Program (OFP) software. The F-15EX platform provides significant operational flexibility, able to perform a wide range of
 mission sets with one or two aircrew.

 F-15EX aircraft have been procured over 6 Lots of aircraft from FY 2020 (Lot 1) to FY 2025 (Lot 6). F-15EX Modification supports retrofits to upgrade early F-15EX aircraft to a common production configuration
 (includes costs for kit procurement, installation, and other supporting requirements) including Conformal Fuel Tank procurement for prior aircraft which were ordered without Conformal Fuel Tanks.

 The first 20 F-15EX aircraft (Lots 1 & 2) delivered with various configurations as new capabilities were cut into the production line. The first 56 F-15EX aircraft (Lots 1 through 4) were ordered without Conformal
 Fuel Tanks.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Aircraft Procurement includes 0 thousand of discretionary and 224,350 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 224,350 thousand.

 FY 2026 mandatory funding supported kit installation of the Lot 1 & 2 retrofit kits, as well as provided for 24 sets of Conformal Fuel Tanks (CFTs), Bomb Rack Units, and associated costs as part of a post-
 production modification to support one operational squadron.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207146F.




