 Justification:
 F-15EX Modification includes retrofit efforts to upgrade the first 20 in-service aircraft (Lots 1 & 2) to a common production configuration and procurement of Conformal Fuel Tanks for previously delivered aircraft.

 Retrofit scope includes procurement of Group A and Group B kit hardware, installation, and recurring and nonrecurring program support costs to update various components and wiring, enabling combat
 capability improvements. Specific retrofits include Multifunctional Information Distribution System - Joint Tactical Radio System Block Upgrade 3 (MIDS-JTRS BU3), Data Transfer Module II (DTM II), the
 ARC-210 Gen 6 radio, Anti-Jam GPS, weapons stores station wiring, cockpit pressure monitor and warning system, along with technical publication updates.

 FY 2027 funding provides for the procurement of 28 sets of Conformal Fuel Tanks (CFTs), Bomb Rack Units, and associated costs as part of a post-production modification.

 Specifically, modification efforts include:
 -SE/GFP Repair: Repair of Government Furnished Property (GFP); supplemental tooling and support equipment (SE) for retrofit line and operating locations
 -Modification NRE: Software/operating systems upgrades to system and applicable support equipment
 -Modification Over & Above: Work discovered during modification that is not within Retrofit scope but necessary to return aircraft to service
 -Data/Training: Updates to technical orders/manuals; technician and operator training
 -Aircraft simulator and training equipment driven by an aircraft modification or a requirement to modify the simulator.
 -DMSMS: Monitoring and resolving Diminishing Manufacturing Sources/Material Shortages and/or obsolescence issues
 -OGCs/PMA/ECOs: Program Office requirements and change order




