 aircraft that is based on the 2-seat F-15QA (Qatar) configuration upgraded with USAF-advanced capabilities.

 Justification: The F015EX, PE 0207146F, BA01 scope of the F-15EX Retrofit effort is to bring twenty (20) in-service aircraft to a common production configuration. The scope of the modifications includes
 procurement of 20 kits that include Group A and Group B hardware, and software installation and recurring and nonrecurring program support costs. Kits and installs include updates to various LRUs and
 associated wiring changes that enable combat capability improvements to MIDS BU3, DTM II, ARC-210 Gen 6, Anti-Jam GPS, weapons stores station wiring, cockpit pressure monitor and warning system, along
 with technical publication updates.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount for F-15EX 3010 BP11 includes 0 thousand of discretionary and 224,350 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 224,350 thousand.

 FY 2027: Funding provides for the procurement of 28 sets of Conformal Fuel Tanks (CFTs), Bomb Rack Units, and associated costs as part of a post-production modification. Installation costs will be addressed
 using prior year funding.


 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207146F.

 Milestone/Development Status

