 Description:
 The F-15 is a versatile 4th-generation fighter aircraft and is central to Combatant Commanders' ability to fulfill National Defense requirements (Joint Lethality in Contested Environments) for numerous operational
 plans (OPLANS) and contingency plans (CONPLANS) in near-peer conflicts. The proliferation of 4th generation enemy aircraft, sophisticated "double-digit" anti-aircraft missile systems, and other threat systems
 pose a significant threat to F-15 survivability.

 The F-15 Eagle Passive Active Warning Survivability System (EPAWSS) ensures future F-15 viability, and replaces the legacy, functionally-obsolete F-15 Tactical Electronic Warfare System (TEWS). F-15
 EPAWSS is an integrated and digital electronic warfare suite which includes electronic detection and identification, geolocation, electronic countermeasures (jamming), and countermeasures dispensing (chaff/
 flares). EPAWSS will significantly improve the F-15's ability to deny, degrade, deceive, disrupt, and defeat Radio Frequency (RF) and electro-optical / infrared threat systems within contested and highly contested
 environments.

 Core Candidate Decision (CCD), dated 10 May 2013, and Depot Source of Repair (DSOR) #13-077F, dated 8 July 2016 and updated 8 August 2023, approved and assigned Warner-Robins Air Logistics
 Complex as the site for organic repair of F-15 EPAWSS hardware and software.

 QUANTITY & INSTALLATION INFORMATION:

 -The Air Force will equip 99 F-15E aircraft with EPAWSS production hardware. Prior-year's funding supports 94 production shipsets, and 2 retrofit efforts (to retrofit the 5 test aircraft initially modified during
 development; modification will be done organically during Programmed Depot Maintenance). FY 2027 will fund 2 additional retrofit efforts, leaving 1 partial retrofit effort to be procured in subsequent years.

 -All 94 full production kits were procured with prior year funding, enabling the Air Force to maximize opportunities for organic installations at Warner Robins Air Logistics Complex (WR-ALC), in parallel with
 installations at the Contractor Modification Facility (CMF) (reference P-3a Installation Information).

 -FY 2024+ funding requested for F-15E EPAWSS installations were aligned to the annual induction schedule to avoid early-to-need funding caused by installation delays (a shift from previous requests which
 funded contractor installations by procurement lot). Resulting from previous delays, prior-year funding accounts for contractor installs into FY 2027.

 -FY 2027 funding will support 16 installations planning to start in FY 2027.

 Milestone/Development Status


