 Description:
 The U-2S Dragon Lady platform is a high-demand/low-density aircraft equipped with modular sensor and data link systems that provided flexibility and mission essential Intelligence, Surveillance, and
 Reconnaissance (ISR) to the Combatant Commands, Joint and Combined forces, and the Intelligence Community in peacetime and wartime. The program supported core missions such as Sensitive
 Reconnaissance Operations (outlined in CJCSI 3250.01) supporting the National Defense Strategy, in addition to other missions that included execution of CCMD OPLANs, CONPLANs, Humanitarian
 Assistance/Disaster Response (HADR), Counter Violent Extremist Organizations, and third-party treaty verification/monitoring via the OLIVE HARVEST mission.

 Procurement funds were used to procure the Advanced Synthetic Aperture Radar System (ASARS).

 There are no requirements for ASARS procurement in FY 2027.

 Justification:
 FY 2027 budget reflects budgeted U-2 divestiture with procurement funds shifted to the Airborne Reconnaissance Systems PE 0305206F. Some of these funds may be obligated by the U-2 program office in
 support of ASARS-2C kitting and fielding and Avionics Technical Refresh efforts, which are a prerequisite to fielding ASARS-2C.




